<HEAD>200 Teens Brought to Courthouse After Loud Party</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WHYNOT, Miss. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A party in Whynot? Why not?
   An estimated 200 teen-agers gathered Friday night in a field near
this town of about 2,000 people 10 miles southeast of Meridian. It
was a going-away party for a friend.
   Authorities, though, told them why not this party in Whynot.
   The party was over when the Lauderdale County Sheriff's
Department received complaints of excessive noise and suspected
alcohol use. In three trips in a school bus, authorities brought the
party-goers to the county courthouse.
   An estimated 75 to 80 teens were issued citations for allegedly
consuming or possessing alcohol, officials said. They were scheduled
to appear in Juvenile Court on Tuesday.
