   The Joneses, former neighbors of Granda's, appeared on the cover
of the group's 1977 album, ``Men From Earth,'' holding the reins of
their mules.
   The two were beaten and robbed in their Boaz home last December,
then left tied up with barbed wire for three days until a neighbor
found them. Clarence Jones remains in a Springfield hospital, and
Roscoe Jones now lives in a nursing home.
   ``The community was outraged, but no one knew what to do about
it,'' said Granda. Perry said organizers hoped to rao Heaven,'' recorded
their last album in 1980 but
still tour regularly.
