<FIRST>r a AM-Knight'sProposal     02-19 0227</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Knight's Proposal,0235</SECOND>
<HEAD>Aspiring Groom Gets A `Yes' With Arthurian Chivalry</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tim Doberstein, a romantic who always
wanted to propose like a knight of old, was relieved when his
girlfriend said ``yes.''
   Otherwise, it would have been a miserable ride in the rain on a
pregnant horse when Doberstein dressed up like a knight to ask
Cheryl Hash to marry him.
   Doberstein, 28, donned the makeshift suit of armor, complete with
a small plastic sword, shield and battle ax on Saturday after
telling Hash, 26, he needed to step out for a few minutes.
   He saddled up Darlin, a small brown horse that's more than six
months pregnant, and rode up to the house while a friend tried get
Hash outside by calling her on a portable telephone. The line was
busy.
   ``Go knock on the door!'' Doberstein screamed at his friend, Ted
Neuner, as neighbors began to stare.
   Neuner tried to phone again and got through. ``Come outside
quick,'' he told Hash.
   Hash emerged from the house and saw the horse riding towards her
with its suited rider.
   ``Oh my God!'' she said as the horse drew near. ``I know that's
you. I recognize your tennis shoes.''
   Undeterred, Doberstein swept down from the horse, bent down on
one knee before Hash and asked her to marry him.
   ``I will,'' she replied.
