<SECOND>AM-Gas Prices,0135</SECOND>
<HEAD>Gas Prices Down Another Quarter-Cent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The national average gasoline price rose 0.25
cent over the past two weeks, according to a survey released Sunday.
   The average cost of a gallon of gasoline, including taxes and
types of pumping service, was 98.78 cents for the week ended Feb.
17, said Trilby Lundberg, editor of the Lundberg Survey, which polls
12,000 gas stations.
   At self-service pumps, average national prices per gallon were
88.45 cents for regular unleaded; 104.62 cents for premium unleaded
and 85.14 cents for regular leaded, Lundberg said.
   At full-service pumps, the regular unleaded average price per
gallon was 118.52 cents a gallon; 130.17 cents for premium unleaded
and 115.04 cents for regular leaded, according to the survey, which
is conducted bi-weekly.
